					<article>
						<h2>How Cell Phones Have Revolutionized the World of Technology</h2>
						<p>At 228.6x127x44.4 mm and weighing 1.1kg the <em>first</em> mobile phone was created by Martin Cooper an engineer at Motorola on April 3rd 1973. However it wasn’t until 10 years later that the first commercial mobile phone was released by Motorola with 30 minutes of talk-time and was capable of storing 30 phone numbers. This life changing technology was called the Motorola DynaTAC 8000x and cost $3995, making it unavailable to the lower and middle class citizen. In the years between 1990 and 1995 the mobile phone started to become a familiar figure in homes. With an estimated cost of $60 to $100 U.S. a month for service fees, Motorola stated that '<abbr title="cellular">cell</abbr> phones would <q cite="http://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/5-major-moments-in-cellphone-history-1.1407352">absolutely not</q> replace standard telephones.'</p>

						<figure><img role="img" src="images/martin-cooper-dynatac8000x.jpg" alt="Martin Cooper with Dynatax 8000X" /></figure>
						<small>&copy; 2012 <a href="http://www.todayifoundout.com/index.php/2012/04/this-day-in-history-martin-cooper-publicly-demonstrates-the-worlds-first-handheld-mobile-phone/" title="Visit Today I Found Out">Today I Found Out</a></small>

						<p>Forty-three years since the first mobile phone was created the cellular phone has skyrocketed in technology. Measuring in at 138.3x67.1x7.1mm and weighing 138g the Apple iphone 7 is only one of the many companies selling mobile phones to the public. Featuring not only a portable wireless telecommunication but also everything an average Joe to a business CEO will need during the day, including a calculator, wireless internet, high definition cameras, 4K digital touch screens, and short messaging service also known as text messaging. Mobile phones in 2016 have an average talk-time of 14 hours and 13 hours of wireless video playback. With the phone reaching <em>97%</em> of U.S. households it is estimated that by 2020 <em>90%</em> of the worlds population over the age of six years old will have a mobile phone. Marking quite the difference from the first commercial mobile phone to the smartphones of today.</p>

						<figure><img role="img" src="images/iphone7.jpg" alt="iphone 7" /></figure>
						<small>&copy; <a href="http://www.reviewgadgets.net/iphone-7-will-continue-colour-variants/" title="Visit Review Gadgets">Review Gadgets</a></small>

						<p>This technology makes keeping in contact as easy as a touch of a button. Now families and friends can reach each other while driving on a long road trip or even shopping in a mall. Kids can even keep in contact with their parents making not only the child feel safer but also the parent when seperated. The use of mobile phones also comes in handy when an emergency arises such as a car accident or an illness making the emergency response more successful. Cell phones all the world to come to you with the touch of a button.</p>
				</article>
